Class PowerUp

java.lang.Object
Mechanics.SnakeObj
Mechanics.PowerUp
public class PowerUp extends SnakeObj
This class provides a powerup object to give the game more variety in difficulty and aids in gameplay.

    • Eaten

      public boolean Eaten(Snake mySnake, javafx.scene.canvas.GraphicsContext g, Tree tree)

      This function resets the powerup location and image. It also ensures that the powerup doesnt spawn within a tree. It does lead to the weird graphical glitch but doesnt inhibit gameplay.

      Parameters:
      mySnake - Takes in the snake object to detect if the snake has collided with the powerup and apply the effect to the snake accordingly - Type Snake
      g - Takes in a graphics context to get the width and height of the canvas - Type GraphicsContext
      tree - Takes in a tree so the resetPU function can use it. - Type Tree
      Returns:
      eatenStatus - Returns true if eaten, false if not - Type boolean
